[<p>Putin tells a meeting of Russia\u2019s cabinet that the commission will provide \u201crapid development and tough control for the effective realization of a national plan on the fight against doping.\u201d</p>, <p>Putin proposed 81-year-old Vitaly Smirnov, an honorary International Olympic Committee member and a veteran of Russian and Soviet sports administration, to lead the commission. Putin said Smirnov has an \u201cabsolutely unimpeachable reputation\u201d and \u201cthe trust and respect of the Olympic family.\u201d</p>, <p>It was not immediately clear if this was the same commission proposed on Thursday by Sports Minister Vitaly Mutko to consider a WADA report alleging state-sponsored doping and cover-ups in Russia.</p>]